					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Ah, I figured there would be some disappointing news about N106; it sounded too good to be true <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />.
<br />
<br />MMC1 seems to have a strange bankswitching scheme. I would prefer as little fixed bank-ness as possible. 8k PRG banks are ideal for me, and what I liked about the N106 is that only $E000-$FFFF is fixed.
<br />
<br />Hmm, Mapper 32 seems to allow for lots of PRG banks, 8k, as the switching register is 8 bits wide. I'm not sure if it can have SRAM/CHR RAM though. Those two things are an even bigger must than anything PRG related. I guess I'll keep looking.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.freewebs.com/the_bott/" class="postlink">-Owner of Poultry Games</a></div>
